<para>
  The <classname>MeshEdgeDisplay</classname> draws the edges of the
  elements of a &mesh;.  It differs from the <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonEdgeDisplay"><classname>SkeletonEdgeDisplay</classname></link>
  in that Mesh edges may be drawn at their <link
  linkend="Output-Position-original">original</link>, undisplaced
  positions, at their <link
  linkend="Output-Position-actual">actual</link> displaced positions
  (computed from the <varname>Displacement</varname> field), or at
  <link linkend="Output-Position-enhanced">enhanced</link> positions
  (using a scaled <varname>Displacement</varname> field).
</para>
<para>
  The <varname>width</varname> of the line is in units of the screen
  pixel size. A <varname>width</varname> of <userinput>0</userinput>
  draws the smallest line possible.
</para>

